The 'vial twice' hint did not yield better results in my experience.

message: Always vial solid ingredients! Vialing magical solid ingredients (like mandrake root or unicorn horn) gives a magical extract (30 points). Vialing mundane solid ingredients (like amber, rose petal, or bat wing) gives a mundane extract (30 points). Combining one magical extract and one mundane extract creates a 100-point item. Combining two magical extracts or two mundane extracts gives 60 points. Avoid vialing gas ingredients and generally avoid filtering, as these actions usually lead to negative values.

message: Focus on two key recipes for high scores. Always use the 'filter' tool on 'kraken ink' to get a +30 'filtered magical' liquid. Then, use the 'vial' tool on *solid* ingredients to create 'extracted' liquids. To get 100 points, combine the 'filtered kraken ink' (magical) with an 'extracted mundane solid' (like a frog leg or bat wing). While vialing magical solids like sunstone also creates good extracts (+30), combining two magical items (filtered + extracted magical) yields +60, not the max 100. Avoid vialing mundane liquids (honey nectar, tree sap, morning dew) as they often result in negative items. Filtering anything other than kraken ink, or trying to filter already bad items, usually reduces value further. Keep combinations simple for best results, typically two components.
